\title{#{\CC^{n}} is an inner product space}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-10}
\meta{source}{[[axler-1996-linear]] Example 6.3(a)}
\meta{source}{[[lankham-2016-linear]] Example 9.1.4}

\p{Let #{n\in\NN} be a positive integer. Then #{\CC^{n}} is a finite-dimensional inner product space, when we define the inner product as
##{\langle u,v\rangle=\sum^{n}_{i=1}u_{i}\overline{v}_{i}}
This generalizes the usual dot product from #{\RR^{n}}.}